{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd3a0af61-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370","identifier":"/us/usc/t11/s1108"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1108"},"text":"§ 1108.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization to operate business","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Unless the court, on request of a party in interest and after notice and a hearing, orders otherwise, the trustee may operate the debtor’s business.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd3a0af62-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2629"},"text":"92 Stat. 2629","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/tIII/s504"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353, title III, § 504","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/384"},"text":"98 Stat. 384","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd3a0af63-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idd3a0af64-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idd3a0af65-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"legislative statements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The House amendment adopts section 1108 of the House bill in preference to the style of an identical substantive provision contained in the Senate amendment. Throughout title 11 references to a “trustee” is read to include other parties under various sections of the bill. For example, section 1107 applies to give the debtor in possession all the rights and powers of a trustee in a case under chapter 11; this includes the power of the trustee to operate the debtor’s business under section 1108.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idd3a0af66-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"senate report no. 95–989","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section permits the debtor’s business to continue to be operated, unless the court orders otherwise. Thus, in a reorganization case, operation of the business will be the rule, and it will not be necessary to go to the court to obtain an order authorizing operation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idd3a0af67-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"house report no. 95–595","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section does not presume that a trustee will be appointed to operate the business of the debtor. Rather, the power granted to trustee under this section is one of the powers that a debtor in possession acquires by virtue of proposed ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s1107"},"text":"11 U.S.C. 1107","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd3a0af68-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idd3a0af69-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, on request of a party in interest and after notice and a hearing,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idd3a0af6a-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idd3a0af6b-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1984 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–353","children":[],"tail":" effective with respect to cases filed 90 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1984","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/353/s552/a"},"text":"section 552(a) of Pub. L. 98–353","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
